narratives.question_text:
What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
(Your anonymous response to this question may be viewed by Yale College students, faculty, and advisers to aid in course selection and evaluating teaching.)
comments: Discussion section for Military History of the West - talked more in depth about course topics.
Knowledge of military history and the reasons for why things happened the way they did.
A deeper understanding of HIST 221 material.

narratives.question_text:
What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
(Your anonymous response to this question may be viewed by Yale College students, faculty, and advisers to aid in course selection and evaluating teaching.)
comments: Good class. I think we had a good discussion section. We went over course themes for each week and the readings. It could be improved by having the reading responses be on the topic that the current weeks readings are for. It was hard to do a response and cite sources from readings we did a week ago as there were so many readings.

Col. Granholm adapted the class well to the online format. I thought pivoting toward pre-class discussion posts was a great choice and allowed the class to not consist of people saying the same thing over and over again vying for participation points. I really enjoyed our discussions.

comments: Group presentations by answering questions was good. Good practice for midterm.
